1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

Programming is used to give instructions to a computer.

Basic building blocks:

Variables

Data Types

Operators

Conditions

Loops

Functions

2️⃣ Important Concepts (with Python Examples)
🔹 Variables

Used to store data

x = 10
name = "Akshay"
🔹 Data Types

int → 10

float → 10.5

string → "Hello"

boolean → True/False

🔹 Operators
a = 10
b = 5

print(a + b)  # Addition
print(a - b)  # Subtraction
🔹 Conditional Statements
x = 10

if x > 5:
    print("Greater")
else:
    print("Smaller")
🔹 Loops
for i in range(5):
    print(i)
🔹 Functions
def add(a, b):
    return a + b

print(add(2, 3))
🧠 Quick Tricks

Variable = storage

Loop = repetition

Function = reusable code

Condition = decision making

